The paper focuses on developing a framework for mobile robots to safely cross street intersections, which falls under the domain of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework utilizes a multimodal convolutional neural network, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The network also involves attention mechanisms (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) for traffic light recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL.
